5.5.23  1:27 pm   Do you consider flowera by miley cyrus to have two choruses? "I can buy myself flowrers..." and "i can love me better..." or do you consider the first to be a long bridge?

      i believe i'd consider that what i call "chorus-superchorus" form. first section is treated with the power of a chorus, and has a lot of lyrics, which lead up to the climactic *title line* which is at the end of that section (chorus) and explodes into the superchorus which will usually be just that crazy infectious *title riff*. (also a sidenote, sometimes what the song thinks is the *title* is different from what the marketing team later decides to title the song, for whatever reason)
